    <section class="hero"><div><p class="eyebrow reveal">Health / Operations / Intelligence</p><h1 class="reveal">Turning messy systems into <em>readable data.</em></h1><div class="hero-copy reveal"><p>I build analytical projects that connect hospital operations, public health data, SQL, BI, machine learning, graph analytics and clear decision support.</p><div class="chips"><span class="chip">Brazilian</span><span class="chip">Remote</span><span class="chip">Relocation</span><span class="chip">Python</span><span class="chip">SQL</span><span class="chip">Power BI</span><span class="chip">NetworkX</span></div></div></div></section>
    <section class="about-panel" id="about"><div><p class="eyebrow">About / Trajectory</p><h2>Engineering, healthcare and data in the same system.</h2></div><div class="about-text"><p>My path started in Biomedical Engineering and moved into Hospital Management, where I learned to read operations as systems: flows, bottlenecks, indicators, risks and decisions.</p><p>At HC-UFU/EBSERH, I work close to clinical pharmacy operations, KPI monitoring and public healthcare routines. I also bring a digital layer from marketing technology, HTML email, content creation, design thinking and AI-supported workflows.</p><div class="about-grid"><article><span>01</span><h3>Healthcare operations</h3><p>Clinical pharmacy workflows, hospital routines, public health data and service performance.</p></article><article><span>02</span><h3>Decision intelligence</h3><p>BI, KPIs, analytical models and communication for practical decisions.</p></article><article><span>03</span><h3>Technical stack</h3><p>Python, SQL, Power BI, machine learning, graph analytics and NLP.</p></article><article><span>04</span><h3>Brazilian context</h3><p>Brazilian professional available for remote roles and open to relocation.</p></article></div></div></section>
    <section class="cloud-section" id="method"><div class="cloud-pin"><div class="cloud-copy"><p class="eyebrow">Scroll / Data Cloud</p><h2>From signals to decisions.</h2><p>The cloud starts as scattered skills and domains. As you scroll, it reorganizes into analytical clusters: health, BI, modeling, graph/NLP and operations intelligence.</p><div class="cloud-actions"><button class="cloud-btn" type="button" id="shuffleCloud">Reshuffle cloud</button><button class="cloud-btn secondary" type="button" id="clusterCloud">Cluster view</button></div></div><div class="cloud-stage" id="cloudStage"><svg class="cloud-line" viewBox="0 0 700 640"><path d="M100 220 C210 110 310 170 400 230 S560 330 610 190"/><path d="M130 420 C250 520 420 500 560 390"/><path d="M210 300 C330 240 450 250 560 310"/></svg><div class="node" style="left:12%;top:18%">healthcare</div><div class="node" style="left:72%;top:15%">SQL</div><div class="node" style="left:38%;top:10%">Power BI</div><div class="node" style="left:84%;top:42%">machine learning</div><div class="node" style="left:18%;top:55%">KPIs</div><div class="node" style="left:52%;top:70%">data quality</div><div class="node" style="left:82%;top:78%">NetworkX</div><div class="node" style="left:28%;top:82%">NLP</div><div class="node" style="left:6%;top:82%">dashboards</div><div class="node" style="left:56%;top:34%">public health</div><div class="node" style="left:24%;top:36%">operations</div><div class="node" style="left:64%;top:54%">decision support</div></div></div></section>
    <section class="tabs-section" id="work"><div class="section-title"><p class="eyebrow">Selected work</p><h2>Cases, method and stack in one interface.</h2></div><div class="tabbar"><button class="tabbtn active" data-tab="projects">Projects</button><button class="tabbtn" data-tab="methodtab">Method</button><button class="tabbtn" data-tab="stack">Stack</button><button class="tabbtn" data-tab="background">Background</button></div><div class="panel active" id="projects"><article class="project"><span class="num">01</span><div><h3>Mapping Primary Healthcare Units in Brazil</h3><p>47,714 Brazilian Primary Healthcare Units analyzed through geographic distribution, coordinate quality and public health data governance.</p><ul><li>Health Analytics</li><li>Geoanalysis</li><li>Data Quality</li></ul></div><a href="https://github.com/luandarodrigues/luandarodrigues/tree/main/projects/ubs-healthcare-mapping">Open ↗</a></article><article class="project"><span class="num">02</span><div><h3>Heart Disease Risk Prediction</h3><p>Clinical machine learning project using 918 records and 11 predictors to evaluate classification models with responsible interpretation.</p><ul><li>ML</li><li>Clinical Risk</li><li>ROC-AUC</li></ul></div><a href="https://github.com/luandarodrigues/luandarodrigues/tree/main/projects/heart-disease-risk-ml">Open ↗</a></article><article class="project"><span class="num">03</span><div><h3>Brazilian E-Commerce Delivery Experience</h3><p>Olist marketplace analysis to understand how logistics, delays, freight, sellers and categories affect customer satisfaction.</p><ul><li>SQL</li><li>Logistics</li><li>Customer Experience</li></ul></div><a href="https://github.com/luandarodrigues/luandarodrigues/tree/main/projects/olist-ecommerce-experience-analytics">Open ↗</a></article><article class="project"><span class="num">04</span><div><h3>CineGraph Network Intelligence</h3><p>TMDB graph analytics project exploring recommendation edges, relationship integrity, streaming coverage and review text signals.</p><ul><li>NetworkX</li><li>NLP</li><li>Graph Analytics</li></ul></div><a href="https://github.com/luandarodrigues/luandarodrigues/tree/main/projects/cinegraph-network-intelligence">Open ↗</a></article></div><div class="panel" id="methodtab"><div class="method-grid"><div class="box"><span>01</span><h3>Frame the decision</h3><p>Define the question, stakeholders, constraints and what a useful answer needs to change.</p></div><div class="box"><span>02</span><h3>Audit the data</h3><p>Check granularity, keys, missingness, duplicates, outliers and business definitions.</p></div><div class="box"><span>03</span><h3>Model the signal</h3><p>Use BI, statistics, ML, graph analysis or NLP depending on the actual decision problem.</p></div><div class="box"><span>04</span><h3>Communicate limits</h3><p>Translate outputs into decisions while making uncertainty, bias and limitations explicit.</p></div></div></div><div class="panel" id="stack"><div class="stack-grid"><div class="box"><span>Analysis</span><h3>Python · SQL · Pandas</h3><p>Data cleaning, exploratory analysis, feature engineering and analytical datasets.</p></div><div class="box"><span>BI</span><h3>Power BI · Looker · KPIs</h3><p>Dashboards, executive reporting, operational monitoring and business metrics.</p></div><div class="box"><span>Modeling</span><h3>Scikit-learn · ROC-AUC</h3><p>Classification, risk analysis, model evaluation and responsible interpretation.</p></div><div class="box"><span>Networks</span><h3>NetworkX · NLP · TF-IDF</h3><p>Graph structure, recommendation networks, review text mining and relationship analysis.</p></div></div></div><div class="panel" id="background"><div class="background-grid"><div class="box"><span>Healthcare</span><h3>Hospital operations</h3><p>Clinical pharmacy workflows, KPIs, public health data and operational decision support.</p></div><div class="box"><span>Education</span><h3>Biomedical Engineering + Hospital Management</h3><p>A foundation that connects systems thinking, healthcare context and data practice.</p></div><div class="box"><span>Public sector</span><h3>EBSERH · 5th place</h3><p>Experience in the Brazilian public healthcare context and hospital operations.</p></div><div class="box"><span>Digital</span><h3>Marketing technology</h3><p>HTML email, content creation, design thinking, automation and AI-supported workflows.</p></div></div></div></section>
    <section class="contact" id="contact"><div><p class="eyebrow">Contact</p><h2>Let’s connect data, operations and decisions.</h2><div class="contact-row"><a class="btn" href="mailto:luandarodrigues30@gmail.com">Email ↗</a><a class="btn ghost" href="https://github.com/luandarodrigues">GitHub ↗</a><a class="btn ghost" href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/luanda-rodrigues">LinkedIn ↗</a></div></div></section>
